H0.text: Only one cell is required for organisms classified as multicellular.

H1.text: Large cells are required for organisms that are classified as multicellular.

H2.text: Organisms that are classified as multicellular must have more than one cell.

H3.text: Identical cells are a requirement for organisms classified as multicellular.

A4.text: A multicellular organism consists of more than one cell

A5.text: A multicellular organism consists of more than one cell, and more than one cell type
